The Supreme Court, Wednesday, upheld the election of Governor Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State. In a unanimous decision, a seven-man panel of justices of the apex court led by Justice Mary Peter-Odili, dismissed as lacking in merit, an appeal the candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, David Ombugadu, filed to challenge the outcome of the March 9 governorship election in the state.  The Supreme Court has also upheld the declaration of Governor Nasir El-Rufai of Kaduna State as the winner of the 2019 governorship election conducted in the state by the Independent Electoral Commission (INEC). The apex court dismissed appeals that sought to nullify their elections.  In similar development, the Apex Court also confirmed the election of Oluseyi Makinde of Kaduna as Oyo State’s governor arch 9th governorship election. The judgement was delivered by Justice Ukaego Mary Peter-Odili CFR who presided over the Oyo State Election Appeal at the Supreme Court in Abuja in the Oyo State Governorship election appeal between Seyi Makinde Vs Adebayo Adelabu.